$D_f=\{(x,y); x > 0 \ \text{ou} \ y \ne 0\}\subseteq \R^2$.
$$\begin{align*}
\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}&= 
\frac{1+\frac{x}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}}{x+\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}= 
\frac 1{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
\\
\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}&=  
\frac{\frac{y}{\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}}{x+\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}
=\frac{y}{x\sqrt{x^2+y^2}+x^2+y^2}
\end{align*}$$

